Executive Team – Carlyle Development Group































































  













			Executive Team		


Piccadilly 


			2017-05-01T06:22:25+00:00		



EXECUTIVE TEAM




Abdi Mahamedi
As Chief Executive Officer of Carlyle Development Group, Mr. Mahamedi provides strategic guidance and leadership for all aspects of the firm’s operations. Following more than 32 years of experience, Mr. Mahamedi has established himself as an astute investor, identifying undervalued assets and emerging real estate trends, and successfully execute on the formulated strategy.
Mr. Mahamedi is a graduate of the University of Pennsylvania in Civil and Structural Engineering (B.S.E 1983, M.S.E 1984). He began his construction career in the United States with Hartz Mountain Industries as a civil engineer for construction of commercial properties. He then moved on to create his own property acquisition and development entities including North American Development, and Emanuel Land Company, a property management and development company, and a subsidiary of Emanuel & Company, a Wall Street investment banking firm. His responsibilities at Emanuel were to assess the engineering and financial feasibility of investment grade development projects, and syndication of real estate partnerships. In late 1987, he joined CDG as a partner, where his responsibilities included the evaluation and supervision of all investment activities.
Moreover, Mr. Mahamedi has also been an active Private Equity investor in the science and technology sector, which in 2005 led him to a large investment in Liquidmetal Technologies (OTC:LQMT), a former NASDAQ listed company (Market Cap of $800,000,000 in 2001), and a leading force in the research, development and commercialization of a revolutionary class of patented alloys and processes with applications in a broad range of medical, military, consumer, industrial, and sporting goods products. Mr. Mahamedi has served on the board of directors since May 2009 in various roles, including Chairman and Vice Chairman, during which the company’s market capitalization has increased from less than $3,000,000 to more than $220,000,000 in 2017.
John Nazemian
Chairman
 Carlyle Development Group
Phone: 914-694-6760
Location: New York, New York
john@carlyle-usa.com
Chairman, John has twenty-five years of experience in construction and real estate investment in the Middle East, France, and the United States. He holds a civil engineering degree (B.S.C.) from London University, 1965. He began his career in the Middle East representing manufacturers of construction equipment including International Harvester. He was also contracted to build roads for the Air Force in Iran. In 1979, he moved to France and through a joint venture with BPGF (French Bank), he invested in and built mid-rise apartment buildings and condominiums in Paris and Fountainbleu. He also developed two recreational mobile home parks in the south of France. At the same time, he invested in land and development projects in the United States, including Houston, Nashville, Florida and Canada. He is one of the founders and principals of Carlyle Development Group. His responsibilities include the supervision of the group’s Land Development Projects in North America, as well as evaluation of investment decisions and arranging equity capital through partnerships with local and foreign investors.Warren Fink
Chief Operating Officer
 Carlyle Development Group
Phone: 914-694-6760
Location: New York, New York
warren@carlyle-usa.com
Mr. Fink has over 40 years experience as a Real Estate professional in Development, Financing, Project Acquisition/Disposition, Asset Management and Debt/Joint Venture structuring. Prior to joining Carlyle as the COO in 2010 he spent five years as the CFO and CIO of The Clarett Group, a residential and mixed use development company in NY with over $2 billion of high rise projects, he had overall responsibility for all operating capital along with project debt and co-investment equity. Prior to Clarett he held senior positions in GMAC Commercial Mortgage, where he established a new division, National Debt/Equity Services; for eleven years he was CIO/partner in Madison Marquette, a lifestyle; retail and mixed use developer responsible for acquisitions, dispositions, debt and equity for a 3 million sq. ft. retail redeveloped portfolio; he was a partner in the Leonard L. Farber Co., a major retail mall developer and founder of the ICSC responsible for development, debt and equity. Mr. Fink spent the first 18 years of his career as a banker and was a manager director of TIAA/CREF responsible for debt and equity investing in the Southeast and Southwestern regions of the U.S. investing with major retail firms as Simon, Rouse, Taubman, General Growth, DeBartolo, Cadillac Fairview, JMB Federated and others.
Mr. Fink holds a Bachelor of Business Administration from Hofstra University.Thomas Fear
Director of Acquisitions 
Carlyle Development Group 
Phone: 914-694-6760
Location: New York, New York
tom@carlyle-usa.com
Thomas Fear joined Carlyle in November 2007 and is responsible for all aspects of management, leasing, acquisitions and development for the firm. Tom has 20 years experience with a broad range of responsibilities as a real estate professional. Most recently, he was a senior vice president with Savills Granite, LLC where he was an integral member of the very successful real estate investment banking firm. At Granite, Mr. Fear was integral in the disposition and financing of over $2 billion of retail, office, and industrial properties encompassing over 30 million square feet. Prior to joining Granite, Mr. Fear served as a residential broker for two years in Manhattan’s Flatiron district. In addition to Mr. Fear’s duties as a broker, he also served as a residential acquisition analyst. Mr. Fear graduated from Roger Williams University in 1991 and received a Masters from New York University with a specialty in Real Estate Finance in 1999.Edward LaGrassa
Senior Asset Management Advisor
Carlyle Development Group 
Phone: 212-461-4274
Location: New York, New York
edlagrassa@earthlink.net
Mr. LaGrassa has had a distinguished career in the real estate industry holding senior positions at major financial service companies and corporations. He is currently president of Chilton Realty Inc. which is a real estate investment, advisory and brokerage company that provides a broad range of commercial services to investors and developers. At Arrow Electronics he headed their global real estate organization with employees 14,000 in 300 locations in 40 countries.
While at Citicorp Ed was the Director of Global Real Estate and was involved in the strategic overview of the banks largest assets. He was co-head of Asset Management and responsible for a varied portfolio of 80 large troubled properties. Prior to Citicorp Ed ran a large diversified portfolio of investment-grade properties at Merrill Lynch Hubbard. He began his real estate career at Allied Stores and during his tenor there he acted as a developer, tenant and landlord for their retail properties and shopping centers.
At the real estate investment firm of Emmes he headed Asset Management, where he oversaw an extensive portfolio of office buildings, shopping centers, industrial properties and raw land. Mr. LaGrassa is a licensed real estate broker and architect. He is an active member of The Urban Land Institute (ULI) at the local district council and with Urban Plan, International Real Estate Group and The Real Estate Board of New York. Ed also chairs the Asset Management Roundtable that BOMA sponsors. He teaches at NYU at the Schack Institute’s masters degree program. He is a member of the board of directors at a NASDAQ listed company and numerous non-profit organizations.Jack Chitayat
Atlantic Realty Group
Phone: 858-459-9922
Location: Lo Jolla, California
JChitayat@gmail.com
Jack began his real estate career in 1992 when he founded Atlantic Realty Group to acquire, own, develop and manage commercial and residential properties in North America. In 1996, Jack Chitayat and Atlantic Realty Group teamed up together with Carlyle Development Group to acquire and manage real estate portfolios in excess of $250 million with over 4 million square feet in the North East, Mid-Atlantic, Midwest, Texas and Canada. Prior to and in parallel to founding ARG, Jack was a Founding Partner of J. Holdsworth Capital Limited, a private investment and management group engaged in the acquisition and subsequent operation of middle market manufacturing, distribution and service businesses, as well as venture-backed start-ups since 1987. His responsibilities at CDG include the evaluation of investment activities in addition to the financing aspects of the acquired portfolio properties. Prior to establishing J. Holdsworth Capital, Mr. Chitayat was a management consultant at Bain & Company. Jack graduated magna cum laude from Tufts University with a Bachelor of Arts degree in Economics and International Relations in 1985.Ali Mohamedi
Director of Construction and Development Management
Carlyle Development Services
Phone: 212-461-4276
Location: New York, New York
amohamedi@carlyledevelopment.com
Director of Construction & Development Management, Ali is a graduate of the University of Pennsylvania in Architecture and Civil Engineering (B.A , M.S.E 1985). He began his career in the United States with Brewran Development Corporation, as both in-house Architect and Development Manager. He progressed to Bovis Lend Lease Inc., where during a ten year tenure, became an Assistant Vice President, and as a Project Executive supervised more than $500,000,000 in high profile construction projects, including the Grand Central Terminal’s main concourse in New York. He then held various senior executive positions at JA Jones, Inc., Structure Tone, Inc. and Tomasso Brothers, during which period supervised a staff of more than 35 employees, and was responsible for more than $500,000,000 in private and public projects. Ali was also a first senior executive member of eBricks.com, where he supervised the development of one of the first construction project management internet portals in U.S., backed by major institutional investors such as Bechtel and GE Capital. He is currently a Managing Partner of AEC Partners, LLC,www.aecpartnersllc.com, an affiliate of Carlyle Development Group. His responsibilities for CDG include the planning and supervision of all pre-development and construction activities.Leon Chudzinski
Sr. Vice President
Development and Construction
Carlyle Development Group 
Phone: 215-416-6168
Location: Philadelphia, PA
leon@carlyle-usa.com
Mr. Chudzinski started with Carlyle in 2016 and has over thirty years of experience in the project development and management of commercial, institutional and multi-family developments. Prior to joining Carlyle, Leon was the Vice President of Construction for the Altman Group of Companies. His responsibilities included business development, pre-construction project planning, tax credit project development, architectural and engineering design coordination and review, construction management and acted as chief estimator. Noted clientele include Aetna, Kraft Foods International, The Community Builders, as well as, various national retail, educational, financial and healthcare institutions. His prior experience includes facilities design and detailing for US Department of Defense contracts for the RCA Corporation, construction project management and as an architectural millwork designer. He holds a bachelor’s degree in Business Management from Rutgers University, CCVTS vocational training and is LEED and OSHA certified. Haig Alejandro Seferian Calvo
President, Carlyle Group Europe
Carlyle Development Group 
Phone: 914-694-6760
Location: New York, New York
alex@carlyle-usa.com
Alex has fifteen years of experience in real estate finance, development and construction in Europe and Latin America. He holds a BA in Economics from Brown University and an MBA from The Wharton School of Finance. Alex began his career as an investment banker, initially at Morgan Stanley in New York and subsequently at Merrill Lynch in London. Over the course of eleven years, he advised on a number of real estate acquisitions and financings. In 2005 he moved to Spain and together with CDG invested in, and began developing residential projects, including an abandoned XII century village which he purchased in 2006. He is one of the founding partners and principals of CDE. His responsibilities for the company include the evaluation and supervision of all investment activities across Europe, with a particular focus on activities in Spain where he is based. Alex speaks fluent Spanish, Portuguese, French and English.
David Viola
Senior Vice President, Property Management Division
Carlyle Development Group 
Phone: 267-324-3570
Location: Philadelphia, PA
david@carlyle-usa.com
David Viola joined Carlyle Development Group in January 2010 as Senior Vice President of its Property Management Division. David brings over 25 years of experience, ranging from the management of world leading manufacturing to high profile commercial facilities. He has been instrumental in transitioning the CDG portfolio from third party to an efficient self-managed structure. David, a Philadelphia native, attended Drexel University after which he served in the United States Naval nuclear power field on board the USS Alexander Hamilton (SSBN-617). Following his service in the US Navy, David spent over 14 years as Director of Facilities and Plant Service Engineering with Spalding Sports Worldwide/Top Flite Golf in Chicopee, Massachusetts. After nearly 15 years of managing a world-leading manufacturer of sports and golf equipment, David transitioned to a career in commercial property management. Joining Pyramid Management Group located in Syracuse, New York as Director of Operations and General Manager of Asset Development, David enhanced his skills to become an effective and dynamic manager of high profile properties like those making up the CDG portfolio. David’s office is currently located at the Public Ledger Building in Philadelphia, one of Carlyle’s premiere assets. From this location, he provides his skills and experience to ensure total, competent operation of this and and all of Carlyle’s North American assets.
He is an active member of ICSC and BOMA, Philadelphia.Mark R. Bradshaw
Vice President; Property Management Division 
Carlyle Development Group 
Phone: 443-438-1479
Location: Baltimore, Maryland
mark@carlyle-usa.com 
Mark has thirteen (13) years of experience in commercial real estate management, development, leasing and marketing. He joined Carlyle shortly after the purchase of the Bank of America Center, in November of 2015. Prior to joining Carlyle, Mark was with Rappaport Management Company, overseeing a portfolio of ten (10) retail and mixed-use properties totaling 800,000+ square feet.
Mark’s previous experience was focused on the Washington D.C. market where he was actively involved in several notable development projects. His proactive management style created close relationships with the local ANC’s (Advisory Neighborhood Committee) and fostered an environment of community involvement, which assisted in the zoning and development efforts for H Street Connection, Skyland Town Center & Apollo H Street. In 2011 Mark was honored to join Gary D. Rappaport on the Mayor’s Streetcar/Streetscape Funding Taskforce, working to bring the Streetcar back to Washington.
Mark currently manages and oversees operations, maintenance, administration and re-development for the Bank of America Building, a retail and office, mixed-use Center, located at 100 South Charles Street in Baltimore, MD.Melainie Eiffert
Vice President; Property Management Division
Carlyle Development Group 
Phone: 410-727-2600
Location: Baltimore, Maryland
melainie@carlyle-usa.com 
Melainie has over 10 years of experience as a Real Estate professional in Asset Management. She began her career with Trammell Crow Company in 2003 and joined CBRE in 2006 as a result of the acquisition of Trammell Crow Company. During her tenure with CBRE, Ms. Eifert held a Asset Manager position and collaborated with the Asset Services team by maintaining positive tenant, vendor and client communication for a varied portfolio of office and retail properties totaling approximately 517,000 square feet. During her 3 years with Carlyle Development Group, Melainie has managed all aspects of Redwood Tower.
Ms. Eifert holds a Bachelor’s Degree from Goucher College in Towson, MD and holds the following industry designations: Leadership in Energy and Environmental Design Green Associate, Real Property Administrator (RPA). Ms. Eifert is a licensed Real Estate Salesperson in Maryland and Virginia.Manu Mahamedi
Director – Planning & Residential Construction
Carlyle Development Group
Phone: 914-694-6760
Location: New York, New York
manu@carlyle-usa.com
Director of Planning & Residential Construction, Manu is a graduate of the University of Pennsylvania in Architecture (M.S. Arch – 1955, B.S. Arch – 1953). He was a partner and majority owner of one of the largest architectural, engineering, and consulting firms in Middle East. His firm designed numerous public works projects including three military bases, three universities with 12,000 students each and an international airport terminal. Mr. Mahamedi’s private and public projects in Iran totaled more than two hundred million dollars in construction costs from 1964 to 1979. Since 1980, he has conducted business in the U.S. as a partner of Brewran Development Group and Empire Homes. Brewran and Empire are builders and developers of luxury condominiums, single-family residences, and commercial buildings.





 
 

 
 
 
 

























Microsoft personalized ad preferences




 













To opt out of personalized ads in this browser, your browser history must allow first-party and third-party cookies and you must have your browsing experience set to NOT delete browsing history on exit. Instructions for enabling cookies and configuring your browsing history may be available in your browsers settings, privacy, or help documentation.

















